# Backend conventions

## Orchestrator

- **`Orchestrator`** owns session state, `audio_queue`, `transcript_queue`, `broadcast`, and agent lifecycle.
- **Coverage preload**: `POST /api/coverage` calls `start_briefing` **without** requiring `/ws/audio`. **`open_session`** preserves ticker/company if already set from coverage.
- **Live path**: `/ws/audio` ‚Üí `open_session` ‚Üí TranscriptAgent; control `phase: listening` ‚Üí `start_live` spawns parallel agents (metrics, sentiment, FinalSynthesisAgent, HighlightLexiconAgent).
- **`ChatAgent`**: `POST /api/ask` only ‚Äî side-channel Q&A; not part of the Live audio task group.

## Agents

- One concern per file under **`agents/`**; export via **`agents/__init__.py`**.
- Use **`google-genai`** / Gemini model names already in use; don‚Äôt swap Live model in `transcript_agent.py` without testing transcription.
- **`tools.py`**: external APIs (Alpha Vantage, FMP, Finnhub); respect rate limits and env vars from `.env`.

## API & WS

- Dashboard: **`/ws`** (outbound JSON); capture: **`/ws/audio`** (binary PCM + control JSON).
- Prefer **structured broadcast** payloads the frontend already handles (`transcript`, `metrics`, `chat`, etc.).
